ok i don't really feel like typing that much but i will anyway. on saturday i watched fireworks and all that good stuff. my daddy and i walked down to the boardwalk to see the sparks fly into the water... pretty. i'll post pictures later. the next day mom woke me up early to go pick up my cousin alicia (), she's a cool kid with rad hair. we went to a fair, i guess it was for the fourth of july. you would not believe the amount of adorable boys we saw. we totally whored it up (not literally, der) and did the whole fair thing, and i went on the gravitron and it kicked ass. yesterday the whole fam went on my cousin's husbands' boat, it's called Only in America. heh, how true (yet sort of sad in a "hey you should think deeper into it" sort of way). that night alicia had to go home... and i played The Used for her in the car, she really liked them. i have to start getting people into good music more often haha... well maybe better music than The Used. then i had today, and that was boring. blah blah blah... bottom line: carneys are dirty, dirty people.

oh yeah, i heard this teenage girl with black dreads at subway today saying "when i grow up, i wanna be a suicidegirl" with this defiant look on her face to a man that looked like her father (he was wearing a sweatervest, if that matters). i almost choked with laughter, it was brilliant. i love random moments like that.

my birthday is september 2nd. i say that all the time, i know, but seriously, i want presents. haha. besides, i'm making you all fabulous tshirts. <3

oh yeah, thursday i get to go to my hometown... birmingham mitch-again, represent. or something like that. it's like, this annoying rich connecticut-like city with an actual downtown. it's so adorable, i heart it, it's like home to me. but you know what i noticed about boca? there is no downtown, it's like, entirely composed of strip malls and nice suburban development apartment housing complexes. ugh. it's all... pink, too. but it's grown on me, and now living up here for the summer, algonac has grown on me too.

it's late. i'm gonna go do something constructive, like watch tv. i miss you kids so much!

xox

okay, here's what really confuses me. sometimes kids will see something that another kid has, or is into, like a certain author, or shirt, or band, or whatever, and then they'll notice what else that kid has, personality wise. and let's say, hypothetically, there's a girl that's pretty and has a lot of friends. she also happens to like a certain band and wear a certain kind of clothes. and then, also hypothetically, other girls notice the popular girl and her friends. now, this kind of popularity isn't the cheerleading-football kind. it's the offbeat, "i go to shows and pierce things and now i'm cool" kind of popularity. and these girls think, "what does she have that i don't? why can't i be like her?" and rush out and buy cd's and makeup and clothes and books and whatever they can find that is just like hers and her friends, in hopes of being scene or whatever. and then, it doesn't work. people don't call the girls who want to be like the popular girl cool or pretty or interesting, like they'd hope. they call them poseurs or something. what does it get those girls, to copy people and fake lives? why would somebody do that? i guess it's low self-esteem, or self-hate, or something inside them that makes them think they're not good enough, like something that happened to them when they were young, or loss of somebody close to them. i don't know, i guess everybody wants to find the best part of themselves, and some people must mistakenly think that the best part of them is somebody else. that's probably where trends come in. why can't you just be yourself? it's not that hard to find something you like personally, and say fuck what everybody else does. it's not like all of this stuff really matters anyway, all of this material stuff. it's impossible to find one "scene" or "label" that you completely fit into without changing yourself, just like it's impossible to find a church with beliefs that you completely agree with. everybody is totally different, so why are there hoardes of people that look exactly the same? this took way longer than i wanted it to. and it doesn't really make sense. but whatever, i think i made my point.

there was horrible pressure to get ready in the morning. bad driving on a one lane road. fry-cook boys yelling at my aunt through the drive through window at mcdonalds. driving by the bank and smiling, because two boys wearing expensive looking shirts and designer jeans are walking in holding hands and carrying mortgage applications. driving five miles out of the way to go to a smoky, greasy diner filled with even smokier, greasier old men and depressed girls working behind the counter. driving down country streets to get to town hall... panic, anger, paperwork & more paperwork, realty and building zones... result in an angry aunt and a somber car ride to the antique store. i found a hitler doll and nazi propaganda (i didn't buy any), a mark ryden passed off as an antique, and told a story to my mother. on to staples for a printer and ink... choices are hard, so i walked next door to barnes and noble. i love book smell. i got a weetzie bat compilation book called dangerous angels (you have to read weetzie bat or else i will hurt you), the new david sedaris (dress your family in corduroy and denim) and my mom got the bill clinton book on audiocassette. we have four or five copies of the hardcover at home, and three copies of the paperback version. there were a large amount of boys in baseball caps buying calvin and hobbes books or arguing over which anime book is better, etc. we drove home through back ways and dirt roads and brown fields, and got lost ... but we made it (obviously.)

once upon a time, in a small marine town, there was this girl that was on vacation. all of her friends were at home and she didn't particularly feel like being with her family 24/7. (she hated when people spelled things with numbers, as well, but i had to add that pop culture reference to preserve the integrity of the story.) one day some woman that was related to her in a way she wasn't sure of gave her a gift in a flashy novelty gift bag. (the gift isn't really worth mentioning, but i think it might be a really good way to use foreshadowing.) the gift was a fake silver charm bracelet with beads in "fun" ocean colors and charms with fish and dolphins on them. the gift bag was a whole other story. it was white and it said (and i quote)

A giRL ALWAys NeeDs NeW sTuff!

and it had a garish cartoon of a woman in a floral dress smiling at an array of sunglasses, lipstick, perfume, shoes, a cell phone, a purse, a cup of coffee, and a slice of cake. the girl accepted the bracelet with a hug and waited until the gift-giver left before tossing away the hideous and distasteful novelty gift bag (which was manufactured by Garven.)

three weeks later, the novelty gift bag mysteriously reappeared on her desk. oooooooo it's a mystery.

the end. (OR IS IT?!?)

that's all i got. nite.

i kept hurting taylor. this was the third time. i don't think you should have to work at a relationship, though. i think it should come naturally, and i had to work at it around him. i sort of put up a front and started feeling depressed after a while every time. he was pretty upset, and i told him he'd find somebody else. (i know he will, too. i know a lot of girls have crushes on him.) but then he said that he didn't want to fall in love ever again. i know that's not true, though. he's young, and he's going to find somebody perfect for him. he thinks i was, but i wasn't. in other news, i'm going to make something pretty as soon as i update this and get offline... oh shit. and do my homework too. fuck fuck fuck. i was watching adult swim last night and laughed the whole fucking way through, that doesn't always happen. but it was great. have you heard of rachel yamagata? fucking beautiful voice. she just came on conan and i looked her up, and she's totally indie. hope she doesn't go the way of coheed and cambria, and modest mouse and join the MTV bandwagon. i swear, that station kills more amazing musicians. i still love coheed... it just doesn't make sense that they would go on MTV of their own accord. this has to be the work of some weird government conspiracy or something.

anyway. this one girl started saying how me not liking MTV and mainstream music made me closed-minded. then she proceeds to diss on the lovely to kill a mockingbird. so i had to say "wow, your taste in music and literature sucks." she made some lame comeback like "thanks."

but seriously, isn't it the other way around? i think people like that are too lazy to get off their fucking asses, turn off the television, and get out of the house and go to a fucking show, or go meet people that don't spend all their free time at the hot topic at the mall. i don't think people like her would know good music if it bit them in the ass, and that's not their fault. i mean, we've all been spoonfed crap since we were in the womb so it's natural to be in the mainstream, it's easy. but what about finding what you really like? i know for a fact not everybody listens to the same shit, because not everybody has the same musical tastes. now, if she really does like hoobastank and yellowcard and linkin park and limp bizkit and evanescence, that's a different story. then it just means she has absolutely horrible taste. but if she's just pretending to, then she's LAAAAAAAAME.

i ran out of things to say.... oh yes. to kill a mockingbird blows all other books out of the motherfucking water. even brackish water! (say that out loud. i'm serious, you'll love it.) ok well i'm going to go now.......................... call me or im me or something and we'll figure out something to do this weekend.

today was mother's day, and seeing as i'm not a mother, i didn't exactly have a blast. i baked my mom a cake (it was very pretty and very yummy. i almost wrote happy fucking mother's day! on it but i didn't feel like making my mom go into cardiac arrest) and i went to see my grandma in the nursing home. i love old people, even though sometimes they make me queasy. i walk in carrying this flower bouquet with a mylar balloon on it for my grandma, and this really really old man says "oh, it's a party!" and i said, "yes, it's mother's day." and he said "oh, i thought it was for the war." i mean, how kickass are old people?! i have no idea which war he was referring to, but whichever war it was, it must have been the best one because there are balloons there. maybe he was thinking of the day all the soldiers came home from wwii and balloons were let loose in the sky and soldiers kissed their girlfriends and etc. so great.
can you imagine? i'm so charitable and good today. last night i completely had ocd of the bedroom and cleaned the whole fucking thing. i have too much time on my hands... oh yes, and i also went to the mall today and to nino's pizza for lunch. i bought some clothes and such... i wanted to go thrifting oh-so-badly but all my shops were closed. i'm going tomorrow after school. since i have nothing better to do, here's a picture of the cake i made...

i've ran out of things to say... tomorrow school starts up again... that's never much fun. i'm going to start concentrating on just doing all my work to make the time go by faster till i can go up north. should be great, i fucking love my little (big) cottage in michigan. it's so quaint. i've been thinking and crying and whining too much lately and i need a vacation so fucking bad. well... i'm off... time to get squeaky clean and take a shower.

xox

i woke up this morning feeling perfectly posey, and ready to start a happy day. i go into my mom's room to say good morning and she says "i hate to do this so early in the morning, but--" and she gives me a grade she got on edline. i have a D in french, when just yesterday i had an A! it totally bites it wrecked my morning. so i threw a childish fit and my mom started yelling at me telling me to grow up and take responsibilities for my grades and that sort of thing (even though i'm in the process of growing up right now, and i do take fucking responsibilities for my grades.) lovely fucking morning i had.

then she tells me after i calm down somewhat that we have absolutely no money until monday so the lunch i'm making tomorrow for my confirmation will have to be made with whatever we have at home. joy and happiness. but it turned out alright, coz she found a $20. yay. i'm gonna make for an appetizer, brie with melted apricots and brown sugar.... a spinach, romaine, tomato, cucumber, and oil and vinegar dressing... fish tacos with mango salsa for the main course... and i dont know what i'm going to make for dessert. i fucking love cooking. it's so fun and relaxing.
